Package org.onyxplatform.api.java.utils

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AsyncCatalog
    AsyncCatalog is a static utility class designed to modify an existing Catalog object by easily adding asynchronous input and output tasks.
    AsyncLifecycles
    AsyncLifecycles is a static utility class designed to allow easy binding of user inputs (vector input segments) to input tasks in asynchronous channels using the Onyx Lifecycle concept and the core-async plugin.
    MapFns
    MapFns is a static utility class used to operate on the main data type used by Onyx, the IPersistentMap.
    Timbre
    The Timbre utility class handles configuration of the log level for a given PeerConfiguration.
    VectorFns
    VectorFns is a static utility class used to operate on a common Onyx datatype, the PersistentVector.
